reason.tex:
%text By definition, \[ \log_b a = c \implies b^c = a \] The above expression is read as \underline\text{$\log$ of $a$ to the base $b$ equals $c$}.
Most of the time, however, we would only be writing $\log a = c$.
It is understood that the logarithm is to the \underline\text{base $e$}
\textbf{Algebra}
% \begin{align} \log (m\cdot n) &= \log m + \log n \\ \log \frac{m}{n} &= \log m - \log n \\ e^{\log m} &= m \\ \end{align}
